    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think this should work, in general we seem to unpack anything list or array-like, but isn't happening on this path.  PR welcome!\r\n\r\nA couple more questionable cases:\r\n```python\r\n\r\nIn [38]: df.loc[i, :]\r\nTypeError: unhashable type: 'Int64Index'\r\n\r\nIn [40]: df.loc[pd.IndexSlice[i.values, 21,], ['height']]\r\nTypeError: unhashable type: 'numpy.ndarray'\r\n\r\n# strangely, this works\r\nIn [39]: df.loc[i.values, :]\r\nOut[39]: \r\n            height\r\nid age sex        \r\n1  22  M       165\r\n2  21  F       152\r\n3  23  M       166\r\n```\r\n"
